  "title": "Avocado Farm",
  "difficulty": "Easy",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">An avocado farmer in California divides his farmland into <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$8$</span> different plots. Each plot of land has a different watering system assigned that will use a variable amount of water. During a recent month, the farmer selects <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$5$</span> random avocados from each plot of land and measures the average weight of the avocado.</div><div class=\"paragraph\">The farmer then compares the average weight (in ounces) to the amount of water used on the specific plot (in gallons). The linear regression model of the data is as follows: </div><div class=\"u-text-align_center\">\n<div class=\"paragraph\"><span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$\\widehat{\\text{weight}} = 2.31 + 0.042(\\text{gallons})$</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\">What is the population of interest for the farmer?</div>",
